Rosatom has moved the deadline for the 6th annual competition of online videos to February 15 due to popular demand. The earlier submission deadline had been set for January 31, 2021. Participants from the age of 18 to 35 residing in African countries are encouraged to post their videos on Facebook and submit their applications to the email atomsforafrica@rosatom.com or by the link to the online submission form. The top three winning videos will be selected by an independent expert panel observing various criteria including original content and creativity, overall quality of the video and content, accuracy and relevance of technical content, as well as ability to clearly communicate the content to an audience. The makers of the top three videos will be rewarded with an all-expenses-paid trip to Russia, where they will get the opportunity to visit several of the countryâ€™s world-renowned tourist attractions as well as various nuclear institutions and advanced nuclear facilities. The Jury includes representatives of nuclear enterprises such as ROSATOM, Nuclear Power Plants Authority (NPPA, Egypt), media practitioners like Influence Communications (Egypt) and regional nuclear NGOs Women in Nuclear South Africa (WinSA), African Young Generation in Nuclear (AYGN) and Nuclear Corporation of South Africa (NESCA). COMPETITION DETAILS What are the rules? Just make a 75-second video, taking into account the formal guidelines below:   POTENTIAL TOPICS FOR VIDEO PRODUCTION (not limited to):  